myAAAMIB.name: myAAAMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

myAAAMIB.description: This module defines my AAA(802.1x) mibs.

myDot1xAuthStatus.name: myDot1xAuthStatus
myDot1xAuthStatus.description: The enable(1)/disable(2) control used by the 802.1x global settings.

myDot1xAuthObjectsQuietPeriod.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsQuietPeriod
myDot1xAuthObjectsQuietPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the quietPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsTxPeriod.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsTxPeriod
myDot1xAuthObjectsTxPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the txPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsSuppTimeout.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsSuppTimeout
myDot1xAuthObjectsSuppTimeout.description: The value, in seconds, of the suppTimeout constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsServerTimeout.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsServerTimeout
myDot1xAuthObjectsServerTimeout.description: The value, in seconds, of the serverTimeout constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsMaxReq.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsMaxReq
myDot1xAuthObjectsMaxReq.description: The value of the maxReq constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsReAuthPeriod.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsReAuthPeriod
myDot1xAuthObjectsReAuthPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the reAuthPeriod constant currently in use by the Reauthentication Timer state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsMaxReauth.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsMaxReauth
myDot1xAuthObjectsMaxReauth.description: The value of the reAuthMax constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsReAuthEnable.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsReAuthEnable
myDot1xAuthObjectsReAuthEnable.description: The enable(1)/disable(2) control used by the Reauthentication Timer state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigTable.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigTable
myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configuration objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each MAC address. An entry appears in this table for each MAC address that may authenticate access to itself.

myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigEntry.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigEntry
myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigEntry.description: The configuration information for an Authenticator PAE.

myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigFdbId.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigFdbId
myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigFdbId.description: The VID of vlan which the address blongs to.

myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigAddr.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigAddr
myDot1xAuthObjectsConfigAddr.description: The MAC address associated with this configurations.

myDot1xAuthObjectsPaeState.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsPaeState
myDot1xAuthObjectsPaeState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsBackendAuthState.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsBackendAuthState
myDot1xAuthObjectsBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsAuthControlledPortStat.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsAuthControlledPortStatus
myDot1xAuthObjectsAuthControlledPortStat.description: The current value of the controlled Port status parameter for the Port.

myDot1xAuthObjectsKeyTxEnabled.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsKeyTxEnabled
myDot1xAuthObjectsKeyTxEnabled.description: The value of the keyTransmissionEnabled constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

myDot1xAuthObjectsIfIndex.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsIfIndex
myDot1xAuthObjectsIfIndex.description: The interface index associated with this configurations

myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsTable.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsTable
myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsTable.description: A table that contains the statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each MAC address. An entry appears in this table for each MAC address that may authenticate access to itself.

myDot1xAuthStatsEntry.name: myDot1xAuthStatsEntry
myDot1xAuthStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE.

myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsFdbId.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsFdbId
myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsFdbId.description: The VID of vlan which the address blongs to.

myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsAddr.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsAddr
myDot1xAuthObjectsStatsAddr.description: The MAC address associated with this states.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolFramesRx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolFramesRx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolFramesTx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolFramesTx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolMyFramesRx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolMyFramesRx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolMyFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL My frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolLogoffFramesRx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolLogoffFramesRx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Logoff frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolRespIdFramesRx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolRespFramesRx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolRespFramesRx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames (other than Resp/Id frames) that have been received by this Authenticator.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolReqIdFramesTx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolReqFramesTx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolReqFramesTx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

myDot1xAuthObjectsInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsInvalidEapolFramesRx
myDot1xAuthObjectsInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the frame type is not recognized.

myDot1xAuthObjectsEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsEapLengthErrorFramesRx
myDot1xAuthObjectsEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

myDot1xAuthObjectsLastEapolFrameVersion.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsLastEapolFrameVersion
myDot1xAuthObjectsLastEapolFrameVersion.description: The protocol version number carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

myDot1xAuthObjectsLastEapolFrameSource.name: myDot1xAuthObjectsLastEapolFrameSource
myDot1xAuthObjectsLastEapolFrameSource.description: The source MAC address carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

myDot1xCurrentUserNumber.name: myDot1xCurrentUserNumber
myDot1xCurrentUserNumber.description: Numbers of users who attached to the system ,regardless of their state.

myDot1xCurrentAuthenticatedUserNumber.name: myDot1xCurrentAuthenticatedUserNumber
myDot1xCurrentAuthenticatedUserNumber.description: Numbers of user who attached to the system and their current state is authorized

myDot1xAccountStatus.name: myDot1xAccountStatus
myDot1xAccountStatus.description: The enable(1)/disable(2) control used by the accounting function.

myAuthIfTable.name: myAuthIfTable
myAuthIfTable.description: The table of the authenticated status of interface.

myAuthIfEntry.name: myAuthIfEntry
myAuthIfEntry.description: The entry of MAC address which can be authenticated.

myAuthIf.name: myAuthIf
myAuthIf.description: The port number of the port/trunk to which frames received from a specific port/trunk and destined for a specific MAC address.

myAuthIfStatus.name: myAuthIfStatus
myAuthIfStatus.description: The authentication status of a port, can be opened by setting its value to Enabled(1), or closed by setting its value to Disabled(2).

myDot1xIfUserMaxTable.name: myDot1xIfUserMaxTable
myDot1xIfUserMaxTable.description: The table of the max dot1x user number on authenticated interface.

myDot1xIfUserMaxEntry.name: myDot1xIfUserMaxEntry
myDot1xIfUserMaxEntry.description: The entry of max dot1x user number on authenticated interface.

myDot1xIfUserMaxIndex.name: myDot1xIfUserMaxIndex
myDot1xIfUserMaxIndex.description: The interface index which dot1x authentication is enabled.

myDot1xIfUserMaxNum.name: myDot1xIfUserMaxNum
myDot1xIfUserMaxNum.description: The max dot1x user num on the interface, this is valid only when dot1x authentication is enable on that interface. Number 0 indicates no user number limits enabled on the interface.

myAAAServerAuthPort.name: myAAAServerAuthPort
myAAAServerAuthPort.description: UDP port used for authentication in the global configuration. For RADIUS only, default value is 1812.

myAAAServerAcctPort.name: myAAAServerAcctPort
myAAAServerAcctPort.description: UDP port used for accounting service in the global configuration. For RADIUS only, default value is 1813.

myAAAServerRadiusKeyStr.name: myAAAServerRadiusKeyStr
myAAAServerRadiusKeyStr.description: The server key to be used with all RADIUS server. Retrieving the value of this object via SNMP will return an empty string for security reasons.

myAAAServerTacplusKeyStr.name: myAAAServerTacplusKeyStr
myAAAServerTacplusKeyStr.description: The server key to be used with all TACACS+ server. Retrieving the value of this object via SNMP will return an empty string for security reasons.

myAAAServerConfigTable.name: myAAAServerConfigTable
myAAAServerConfigTable.description: This table shows current configurations for each AAA server, allows existing servers to be removed and new ones to be created.

myAAAServerConfigEntry.name: myAAAServerConfigEntry
myAAAServerConfigEntry.description: The table of AAA server configuration identified by its protocol and its index.

myAAAServerConfigProtocol.name: myAAAServerConfigProtocol
myAAAServerConfigProtocol.description: The variable denotes the protocol used by the managed device with the AAA server corresponding to this entry in the table.

myAAAServerConfigIndex.name: myAAAServerConfigIndex
myAAAServerConfigIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each server. If the myAAAServerConfigIndex value for row creation is already in use by an existing entry, snmp set to the myAAAServerConfigIndex value will fail. Upon reload, casIndex values may be changed.

myAAAServerConfigAddressType.name: myAAAServerConfigAddressType
myAAAServerConfigAddressType.description: The type of address format used for the myAAAServerConfigAddress object.

myAAAServerConfigAddress.name: myAAAServerConfigAddress
myAAAServerConfigAddress.description: The IP address of the server.

myAAAServerConfigAuthPort.name: myAAAServerConfigAuthPort
myAAAServerConfigAuthPort.description: UDP/TCP port used for authentication in the server. For RADIUS, default value is 1812. For TACACS+, default value is 49.

myAAAServerConfigAcctPort.name: myAAAServerConfigAcctPort
myAAAServerConfigAcctPort.description: UDP/TCP port used for accounting service in the server. For RADIUS, default value is 1813. For TACACS+, the value of myAAAServerConfigAcctPort is ignored, myAAAServerConfigAuthPort will be used instead.

myAAAServerConfigKeyStr.name: myAAAServerConfigKeyStr
myAAAServerConfigKeyStr.description: The server key to be used with this server. Retrieving the value of this object via SNMP will return an empty string for security reasons.

myAAAServerConfigRowStatus.name: myAAAServerConfigRowStatus
myAAAServerConfigRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. Once the entry status is set to active, the associated entry cannot be modified except destroyed by setting this object to destroy(6).

myAuthAddrTable.name: myAuthAddrTable
myAuthAddrTable.description: The table of MAC address which can be authenticated.

myAuthAddrEntry.name: myAuthAddrEntry
myAuthAddrEntry.description: The entry of MAC address which can be authenticated.

myAuthPort.name: myAuthPort
myAuthPort.description: The port number of the port/trunk to which frames received from a specific port/trunk and destined for a specific MAC address.

myAuthMacAddress.name: myAuthMacAddress
myAuthMacAddress.description: The MAC address which can be authenticated.

myAuthAddrStatus.name: myAuthAddrStatus
myAuthAddrStatus.description: valid(1) - this entry is currently in use . invalid(2) - writing this value to the object removes the corresponding entry.

myAuthUserTable.name: myAuthUserTable
myAuthUserTable.description: The table of authentication User Info.

myAuthUserEntry.name: myAuthUserEntry
myAuthUserEntry.description: The entry of authentication User Info table.

myAuthUserFdbId.name: myAuthUserFdbId
myAuthUserFdbId.description: The VID of vlan which the address blongs to.

myAuthUserMacAddress.name: myAuthUserMacAddress
myAuthUserMacAddress.description: The MAC Address of authentication User .

myAuthUserSessionId.name: myAuthUserSessionId
myAuthUserSessionId.description: The Session Id of authentication User .

myAuthUserIpAddr.name: myAuthUserIpAddr
myAuthUserIpAddr.description: The IP Address of authentication User .

myAuthUserStatus.name: myAuthUserStatus
myAuthUserStatus.description: Setting this object to 'invalid' will close a authenticated user, set its value to valid will cause no action of agent, when query always return value valid.

myAuthUserForVPNDel.name: myAuthUserForVPNDel
myAuthUserForVPNDel.description: VPN user's name. Setting this object will delete a authenticated user and this user is unauthenticated. The set string is the username. Reading this object always return null string.

myIpAuthorizationMode.name: myIpAuthorizationMode
myIpAuthorizationMode.description: disable(1) - don't limit ip address of user dhcpServer(2) - limit ip address of user, only ip address assigned by the dhcp server is legit. radiusServer(3) - limit ip address of user, only ip address assigned by the radius server is legit. supplicant(4) - mac+ip+port indicates different users (get the IP adress through supplicant)

myClientProbeEnabledStatus.name: myClientProbeEnabledStatus
myClientProbeEnabledStatus.description: The status of client probe function.

myClientProbeHelloInterval.name: myClientProbeHelloInterval
myClientProbeHelloInterval.description: The interval that client send hello packets.

myClientProbeAliveInteval.name: myClientProbeAliveInteval
myClientProbeAliveInteval.description: When switch does not receive any legal hello packets from client in this interval,it will send RADIUS-Account-Stop to RADIUS server to stop this connection.The value of the objects must be more than myClientProbeHelloInterval

myAAAMIBCompliance.name: myAAAMIBCompliance
myAAAMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the My AAA MIB

myDot1xAuthMIBGroup.name: myDot1xAuthMIBGroup
myDot1xAuthMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing dot1x authentication managment.

myAAAServerMIBGroup.name: myAAAServerMIBGroup
myAAAServerMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing AAA server managment.

myAuthAddrMIBGroup.name: myAuthAddrMIBGroup
myAuthAddrMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing address permitted authentication managment.

myAuthModeMIBGroup.name: myAuthModeMIBGroup
myAuthModeMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing authentication mode managment.

myClientProbeGroup.name: myClientProbeGroup
myClientProbeGroup.description: A collection of objects providing client probe management.
